ul.li:
2010-05-08T19:00:00Z : Found it by Fitzet
This was a 'Windsockers' themed day of cache finds around the airport. This was #7 of 7.
We stopped at stage 2 for a well earned beverage. Pub themed caches are great! The final location was very interesting too, thanks for bringing us here.
SL TFTC

2010-04-20T19:00:00Z : Found it by dsquaredd2
After a very long hike 2 days ago to collect the information, we collected it at during the biggest caching day for D2D2 today with a cache run with the owner, Windsockers! We went on a circuit beginning with Newgrange and ending in the Skerries finding and maintaining caches. A fun day, each location was unique. I was standing right there when I made the first lap. Man! This was the twenty-fourth. TFTC!

2010-03-07T20:00:00Z : Found it by John NW
Nice cache - however the clue at the final part had me searching in the wrong place - i do take these things so literally!!!! TNLN TFTC

2010-03-06T20:00:00Z : Found it by niripas
Had fun with this cache [:)] TFTC!

2010-03-06T20:00:00Z : Found it by Spark_ie
Had the co-ords worked out a while ago, but this was my first time in the neighbourhood since. Initially thought the cache was missing, but an SOS call sent me in the right direction. TFTC, Spark_ie
